{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603604"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:40:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:40:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15771"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15771"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.69,0.17,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8462"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70433"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8462","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8462"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15771"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55897"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"112"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7065"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20349"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20352"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70433","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70433"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 75-year-old man is diagnosed with prostate cancer with metastases to the ileum and sacrum.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes why metastases to the vertebrae are common in prostate cancer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The close proximity of the prostate to the sacrum","Valveless prostatic and rectal venous plexi communicate with the vertebral venous plexus","Prostatic and rectal venous plexi drain into the internal iliac vein","Perforation of the rectovesical septum allowing metastases into the rectum","Increased pressure in the prostatic venous system due to the drainage angle"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Evalveless prostatic and rectal venous plexi communicate with the vertebral venous plexus\u003C/strong\u003E. Known as Batson\u0027s plexus, the absence of valves allows bidirectional flow of blood. While \u003Cstrong\u003Eprostatic and rectal venous plexi drain into the internal iliac vein\u003C/strong\u003E, this is not the mechanism for vertebral metastases. \u003Cstrong\u003EThe close proximity of the prostate to the sacrum\u003C/strong\u003E is not the primary reason for the pattern of spread.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerforation of the rectovesical septum\u003C/strong\u003E is not a typical mechanism of metastatic spread. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased pressure in the prostatic venous system\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003Edue to drainage angle\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Prostate cancer commonly metastasizes to vertebrae via Batson\u0027s plexus - a valveless venous network connecting prostatic and vertebral vessels.","The absence of valves in these venous plexi allows bidirectional blood flow, facilitating metastatic spread."],"references":["Sekhoacha M, Riet K, Motloung P, Gumenku L, Adegoke A, Mashele S. Prostate Cancer Review: Genetics, Diagnosis, Treatment Options, and Alternative Approaches. Molecules. 2022 Sep 5;27(17):5730. doi: 10.3390/molecules27175730. PMID: 36080493; PMCID: PMC9457814.","Manna F, Karkampouna S, Zoni E, De Menna M, Hensel J, Thalmann GN, Kruithof-de Julio M. Metastases in Prostate Cancer. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med. 2019 Mar 1;9(3):a033688. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a033688. Erratum in: Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med. 2018 Jul 2;8(7):a035568. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a035568. PMID: 29661810; PMCID: PMC6396340.","Ziaee S, Chu GC, Huang JM, Sieh S, Chung LW. Prostate cancer metastasis: roles of recruitment and reprogramming, cell signal network and three-dimensional growth characteristics. Transl Androl Urol. 2015 Aug;4(4):438-54. doi: 10.3978/j.issn.2223-4683.2015.04.10. PMID: 26816842; PMCID: PMC4708593."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55897"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15771"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55897","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55897"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T11:44:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-15T19:06:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8462"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70433"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"36","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/36"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"desc